{"data":[{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"1","text":"How 1:1 This chapter is an acrostic poem, each verse beginning with the successive letters of the Hebrew alphabet. lonely lies the city,"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"2","text":"She weeps aloud in the night,"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"3","text":"Judah has gone into exile"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"4","text":"The roads to Zion mourn,"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"5","text":"Her foes have become her masters;"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"6","text":"All the splendor has departed"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"7","text":"In the days of her affliction and wandering"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"8","text":"Jerusalem has sinned greatly;"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"9","text":"Her uncleanness stains her skirts;"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"10","text":"The adversary has seized"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"11","text":"All her people groan"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"12","text":"Is this nothing to you, all you who pass by?"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"13","text":"He sent fire from on high,"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"14","text":"My transgressions are bound into a yoke,1:14 Most Hebrew manuscripts; other Hebrew manuscripts and LXX He kept watch over my sins"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"15","text":"The Lord has rejected"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"16","text":"For these things I weep;"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"17","text":"Zion stretches out her hands,"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"18","text":"The LORD is righteous,"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"19","text":"I called out to my lovers,"},{"book":"Lamentations","chapter":"1","verse":"20","text":"See, O LORD, how distressed I am!"},